      • removeIndex

        public static int[] removeIndex(int[] original,
                                int index)
        Method removeIndex removes given index value from given array. Copies numbers from the original list to the temp one until iteration reaches the index given. When reaches index, skips to the next index at the original list and continues copy from there on. Thus, the temp array is one shorter than original one.
        Parameters:
        original - argument, that gives the array from where to remove a number
        index - argument shows, which index is to be cleaned out
        Returns:
        int array one index smaller than the one that was given as a parameter

      • sort

        public static int[] sort(int[] array)
        Method sort is used for sorting int array in ascending order. Method sorts the given array by repeatedly finding the minimum element from the unsorted part of the array. In every iteration of the method, the minimum element from the unsorted part is picked and moved to the index at hand in sorted part.
        Parameters:
        array - argument, that holds the int array to be sorted.
        Returns:
        given int array after it has been sorted.

      • intArrIntoString

        public static java.lang.String intArrIntoString(int[] array,

        Method intArrIntoString converts int array into string format. Method converts int array into String array by calling method createStringArr and then it iterates through that String array, and adds every array item with suffix into a string.
        Parameters:
        array - an argument, which contains the int array to be converted
        prefixLength - an argument, which tells how many chars are in the prefix
        Returns:
        String

      • checkPrior

        public static int[] checkPrior(int backUp,
                               int[] howManyYears,
                               int years)
        Method checkPrior is used for checking the right numbers so far. It iterates through given int array from given index backwards toward the array's first index. If it comes across default value (-1) it changes that index's value into the given years.
        Parameters:
        backUp - is argument, that tells the backing up start point
        howManyYears - is the given int array
        years - is the years that will be added to the default bearing index
        Returns:
        int array with fixed index values
